{
  "texts": [
    "In the literature, this has also been referred to as subtraction scheme or normal-ordering prescription.",
    "For this example, the Hartree correction is momentum-independent.",
    "One example where the choice of ρ 0 is natural and agreed upon in the literature is semiconducting moiré TMDs, which exhibit an eV scale band gap at charge neutrality.",
    "In this case ρ 0 corresponds to the neutrality state obtained by fully filling the valence bands.",
    "Note that these potentials are not due to virtual (particle-hole) excitations between active and frozen states."
  ]
}